BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 171.6 720 Td (Chapter 1: Life in the Ocean) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Deep in the sparkling blue ocean lived a tiny water droplet named Droplet.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (She was one of billions and billions of water droplets in the enormous sea.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (Droplet loved swimming with the fish and riding the ocean waves.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('I wonder what is beyond the surface?' Droplet thought one sunny day.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (She had heard stories from older droplets about amazing adventures above the water.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('Someday, I will go on my own big adventure!' Droplet promised herself.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: OUR OCEANS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Oceans cover about 71% of Earth's surface - that is almost three-quarters!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (There are five main oceans: Pacific, Atlantic, Indian, Southern, and Arctic.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (The Pacific Ocean is the biggest - it is larger than all the land on Earth combined!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Ocean water is salty because rivers wash minerals from rocks into the sea.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (About 97% of all water on Earth is in the oceans. Only 3% is freshwater!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* The ocean is home to over 230,000 known species of animals and plants.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* The deepest point in the ocean is the Mariana Trench - 36,000 feet deep!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* If you could drive a car to the bottom of the ocean, it would take about 7 hours.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Fill a glass with water and add 2 tablespoons of salt. Taste it - that is like ocean water!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (If most of Earth is covered by water, why is fresh water so precious?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
