BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 205.2 720 Td (Chapter 2: Rising Up!) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (One hot summer day, the Sun beat down on the ocean surface with powerful rays.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (Droplet felt herself getting warmer and warmer and warmer!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('What is happening to me?' she exclaimed as she began to feel lighter.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (Suddenly, Droplet was floating UP! She was turning into invisible water vapor!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('I am evaporating!' she shouted with excitement. 'I am becoming a gas!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (Higher and higher she rose, leaving the ocean far below. The adventure had begun!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: EVAPORATION) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Evaporation is when liquid water turns into water vapor \(an invisible gas\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (The Sun's energy heats water molecules, making them move faster and faster.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (When molecules move fast enough, they escape from the liquid into the air!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Evaporation happens from oceans, lakes, rivers, puddles - even your wet laundry!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Warm air can hold more water vapor than cold air. That is why hot days feel humid.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* About 90% of water in the atmosphere came from ocean evaporation.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* Evaporation is happening right now from every body of water on Earth!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Hot water evaporates faster than cold water because molecules move faster.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Put a shallow dish of water in the sun. Mark the water level. Check it the next day!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (Why do puddles disappear on sunny days? Where does the water go?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
