BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 176.4 720 Td (Chapter 3: Becoming a Cloud) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (High up in the sky, the air was much colder. Droplet started to shiver.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td ('Brrr! It is freezing up here!' She felt herself changing again.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (The cold air turned her back from invisible vapor into a tiny visible droplet!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (She looked around and saw millions of other droplets gathering together.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('We are forming a cloud!' her new friends cheered.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (Together, they made a big, fluffy, white cloud floating across the blue sky.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: CONDENSATION & CLOUDS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Condensation is the opposite of evaporation - gas turns back into liquid.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (When warm, moist air rises and cools, water vapor condenses into tiny droplets.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Clouds are made of billions of tiny water droplets or ice crystals.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Each droplet forms around a tiny speck of dust or pollen in the air.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Different cloud shapes tell us about the weather that is coming!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* An average cloud weighs about 1.1 million pounds! It floats because it is spread out.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* You can see condensation on a cold glass of water on a hot day.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Fog is actually a cloud that forms close to the ground!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Breathe onto a cold window - the fog you see is condensation from your warm breath!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (If clouds are so heavy, why do they float in the sky?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
