BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 195.60000000000002 720 Td (Chapter 4: The Big Fall) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (The cloud grew bigger and bigger as more water droplets joined.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (It turned from white to gray and then to dark, heavy gray.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('I am getting too heavy to stay up here!' Droplet cried.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td (WHOOSH! She fell from the cloud, tumbling down through the air!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td ('WHEEEEE! I am rain!' Droplet laughed as she fell faster and faster.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (All around her, millions of other droplets were falling too. It was raining!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: PRECIPITATION) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Precipitation is any water that falls from clouds: rain, snow, sleet, or hail.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Raindrops form when tiny cloud droplets bump together and grow bigger.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (When droplets get too heavy for the air to hold up, they fall as rain!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (If it is cold enough, water freezes into snowflakes or ice pellets \(sleet\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Hailstones form when raindrops get pushed up in a storm and freeze over and over.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* A raindrop falls at about 14 miles per hour \(faster if the drop is bigger\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* The wettest place on Earth gets about 467 inches of rain per year!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Raindrops are not actually teardrop-shaped - they look more like hamburger buns!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Put a cup outside when it rains. Measure how much water collects in one hour!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (What makes it snow instead of rain? What is the difference?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
