BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 171.6 720 Td (Chapter 5: Down the Mountain) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (SPLASH! Droplet landed on the top of a tall mountain.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (She joined a tiny trickle of water running down the rocky slope.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (More and more droplets joined until the trickle became a stream!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('We are getting stronger together!' Droplet cheered as they flowed faster.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (The stream became a river, winding through valleys and past towns.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td (Droplet could feel herself slowly wearing away the rocks beneath her.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: RIVERS & EROSION) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (Rivers start as small streams high in the mountains from rain or melting snow.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Gravity pulls water downhill, making it flow from mountains toward the ocean.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (Erosion is when flowing water wears away rock and soil over time.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (The Grand Canyon was carved by the Colorado River over millions of years!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (A watershed is all the land area that drains water into a particular river.) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* The Nile River in Africa is the longest river in the world \(4,130 miles\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* Rivers carry tiny bits of rock and soil all the way to the ocean.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* Water always flows downhill - it follows the path of least resistance.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Pour water on a pile of sand or dirt. Watch how it carves channels - that is erosion!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (How did the Grand Canyon form? How long do you think it took?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
