BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 166.8 720 Td (Chapter 6: Underground Secret) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (Some of Droplet's friends did not stay in the river. They soaked into the ground!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (Droplet decided to follow them on this underground adventure.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td (She seeped through soil, squeezed between grains of sand, and went deeper.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('It is dark down here!' Droplet said. 'But I can feel other water all around me.') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (She had found a hidden underground lake called an aquifer!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('So this is where some drinking water comes from!' Droplet realized.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: GROUNDWATER) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (When rain soaks into the ground, it becomes groundwater.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (Groundwater fills the spaces between soil particles and cracks in rocks.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (An aquifer is a layer of rock or sand that holds lots of groundwater.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Wells are holes drilled down to reach aquifers so people can pump up clean water.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Groundwater can stay underground for thousands of years before resurfacing!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 390 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 449 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 429 Td (* About 30% of the world's freshwater is groundwater \(most freshwater is in ice!\).) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 411 Td (* Springs happen when groundwater naturally flows out of the earth.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 393 Td (* It can take a single drop of water 10,000 years to travel through a large aquifer.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 360 Td (TRY THIS!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 344 Td (Fill a clear cup with small rocks. Slowly pour water in - watch it fill the spaces between rocks!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 72 324 Td (THINK ABOUT IT:) Tj ET
BT 0.2 g /F4 10 Tf 82 308 Td (Where does the water in your home come from? A well, a river, or a lake?) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
