BT 0 g /F2 20 Tf 171.6 720 Td (Chapter 8: Back to the Ocean) Tj ET
q 0.5 G 1 w 72 710 m 540 710 l S Q
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 680 Td (After her time as cloud, rain, river, groundwater, and tree visitor,) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 664 Td (Droplet finally flowed back into the great blue ocean where she started!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 648 Td ('I am home!' Droplet cheered, reuniting with her ocean friends.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 632 Td ('Tell us about your adventure!' they cried. 'Where did you go?') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 616 Td (Droplet told them everything. 'And the best part?' she smiled.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 600 Td ('I will do it all over again! The water cycle never, ever stops!') Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 13 Tf 72 564 Td (THE SCIENCE: THE WATER CYCLE NEVER ENDS) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 544 Td (The water cycle has been running for billions of years without stopping!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 528 Td (The water you drink today might have been dinosaur bathwater millions of years ago!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 512 Td (No new water is created - the same water just keeps cycling over and over.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 496 Td (Evaporation, condensation, precipitation, collection - round and round it goes.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 11 Tf 72 480 Td (Every living thing on Earth depends on the water cycle to survive.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F2 14 Tf 72 444 Td (MORAL:) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F5 13 Tf 72 424 Td (Everything in nature is connected - even a tiny droplet matters!) Tj ET
q 0.92 g 67 335 478 89 re f Q
BT 0 g /F2 11 Tf 77 394 Td (SCIENCE FACT BOX) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 374 Td (* Earth has the same amount of water now as when dinosaurs roamed the planet!) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 356 Td (* Only about 0.3% of all water on Earth is usable freshwater for humans.) Tj ET
BT 0 g /F4 10 Tf 82 338 Td (* It takes about 9 days for a water molecule to complete the cycle from evaporation to rain.) Tj ET

endstream
endobj
